intment toward the child. Her movements are slow and careful, focused on comfort rather than urgency.\n\nShe gently opens the neckline of the girl’s ruffled nightgown and begins rubbing the ointment onto the child’s upper chest. The child remains still, looking downward and then relaxing. In a close view, the woman’s hand moves in smooth strokes over the girl’s chest, just below the collarbone, while the doll’s face is visible beside them. The girl’s expression softens; her eyes drift partly closed and her mouth settles into a small, contented smile. The adult hand continues the rubbing motion across the chest, then eases away as the child tilts her chin slightly upward, appearing soothed.\n\nThe view widens again to the bedside scene. The woman in green finishes adjusting the girl’s nightgown and blanket, still smiling. The girl sits more upright in bed, and the woman’s hands rest reassuringly on her shoulders and chest area. The woman then looks outward toward the viewer with a composed, maternal expression while keeping one hand protectively on the child. The girl leans closer to her, and the woman gathers her into a hug. The little girl sits up within the white covers, nestled against the woman’s chest. The woman kisses the child on the forehead or temple, then both smile. The child cuddles in, clutching close to the woman, and the woman beams directly outward before looking down affectionately at the girl.\n\nA bedside lamp fills the scene next. It has a pale lampshade and a shiny, dark metal base. A hand reaches under the shade near the switch, fingers sliding around the lamp stem as if turning it off or adjusting it for bedtime, then withdraws. The lamp remains the central object for a moment, reinforcing the nighttime setting.\n\nThe final view settles on the Vicks VapoRub jar placed on a polished bedside table in front of the lamp base. The jar is dark blue or black with a pale greenish lid and a cream-colored label. The label reads “Vicks VapoRub,” with smaller text below including “Vaporizing Ointment” and “Relieves distress of colds.” At the very end, large white words appear to the right of the jar: “most comforting thing you can do for a cold.” The product remains prominently displayed beside the warm bedside lamp, visually linking it with nighttime care and comfort.",
